The suit was apparently inspired by the capital’s most famous fictional tweed-wearing detective, Sherlock Holmes. 

The colour scheme is an urban grey with accents of blue and gold running through, and the suit has apparently been tailored to fit Tinie’s contemporary urban style. 

Curators have recorded the entire suit-making process from sketch to stitch and the suit will become part of the museum’s extensive fashion and textiles collection to help document historical and contemporary menswear in London today. 

